  "engines": ["Ouie"],
  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Phase Distortion (voice 1, algoParam=0.72) + Additive (voice 2, rich harmonics). HAMMER=-0.1 — on the STRIFE side of neutral, just barely. PD's phase-warped waveshape contains specific harmonic emphasitions (like a Casio CZ organ) that clash productively with additive's pure sinusoidal partials at near-neutral HAMMER. The result is cathedral-scale: massive, ancient, slightly unresolved. The -0.1 position means the voices never fully agree — a permanent, beautiful tension.",
  "tags": ["ouie", "phase-distortion", "additive", "cathedral", "organ", "aether", "neutral-strife", "vintage"],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "Phase distortion is the shadow of a sine wave — the same shape, differently bent.",
      "Additive is the pure harmonic series. PD is its distorted echo.",
      "At -0.1, they are almost at peace. Almost."
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "Try moving algoParam1 (PD depth) from 0.2 to 0.9 to hear how the phase warp changes the HAMMER interaction. Low PD depth behaves like VA. High PD depth creates Casio-organ-style resonance peaks that fight the additive harmonics even at near-neutral HAMMER.",
    "diagnosis": "PD+Additive is underexplored in the factory set. The CZ-style phase warp creates specific partial skews that don't exist in VA or FM — unique interaction territory with additive at near-neutral HAMMER. Long attack (0.15s) and long release (2.5s) emphasize the cathedral scale. BP filter on voice 2 creates a mid-presence peak that projects through mixes."
  },
